review_blob: Straight out of the can. You get what you pay for. It was cheap and tastes that way. Nothing subtle here !. Certainly not tasteless, just what is that taste or smell ? Lots of corn and I guess some hops but, a bit too much skunk. Good just to get smashed on.

A very thick and lasting head. Its the reddish coppery color described on the commercial. Taste is much smoother and easier than I imagined. Very drinkable. An almost mediciney taste. I enjoyed it. I will get it again.
beer_name: Mendocino Eye of the Hawk Select Ale

review_blob: I am getting jaded. I tried this for my first time on tap years ago and it changed my life. Lately, I tried the bottle and something is lost in the translation. Bottle is good but, not earth shattering
Not bad for a cheap beer, not bad at all. Not memorable either. Pours and aroma are fine, just when you taste it, you remember how low the price was.
Bought at Trader Joes in RPV. Nothing special but, not bad for its price. Cheap beer basically
